      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are often used as a tool to shield domestic industries from foreign competition, but they frequently result in higher prices for consumers and can trigger trade wars. While they may protect local manufacturers in the short term, they often lead to inefficiencies and reduced economic growth overall. Ultimately, the debate centers on whether the temporary protection of specific industries outweighs the long-term costs imposed on the broader economy.",
